(17, 'Arsenal’s Trouble Deepens As Koscielny Gets Sidelined For 3 Weeks', 'http://www.thetrentonline.com/?p=124016', 'Uncategorized', '<p>Arsenal will have to cope without French centre back, Laurent Koscielny when they face Manchester...', '<div class="pf-content"><p style="text-align: justify;">Arsenal will have to cope without French centre back, Laurent Koscielny when they face Manchester United on Sunday, October 4, 2015 in the English Premier League. The 30-year-old defender was replaced by Per Mertesacker in the Gunners’ 2-3 defeat to Olympiakos in the Champions League after he sustained a hamstring injury.</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Arsenal manager, Arsene Wenger during his press conference on Friday, October 2, 2015 confirmed that Koscielny will be missing in action for about three weeks. The defender will also miss France’s international friendlies against against Armenia and Denmark on October 9 and 12 respectively.</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">This comes as sad news to Gunners fans as Mathieu Flamini and Mikel Arteta have also been ruled out of the Manchester United game.</p>\n</div><p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.thetrentonline.com/arsenals-trouble-deepens-koscielny-gets-sidelined-3-weeks/">Arsenal&#8217;s Trouble Deepens As Koscielny Gets Sidelined For 3 Weeks</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.thetrentonline.com">The Trent</a>.</p>\n', '2015-10-03 08:17:40', '2015-10-03 07:30:41', 10, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'http://www.thetrentonline.com/arsenals-trouble-deepens-koscielny-gets-sidelined-3-weeks/', 0, 0, 0, '2015-10-03 08:17:40', 2, 1, NULL, 0, NULL, 'Arsenal’s-Trouble-Deepens-As-Koscielny-Gets-Sidelined-For-3-Weeks'),
(18, 'Ministerial Nominees: Okorocha’s Cousin, Oyinlola Make Buhari’s 2nd Batch – Reports', 'http://www.thetrentonline.com/?p=124125', 'Politics,Jokes and Fun,Governance,,', '<p>There are strong indications that President Muhammadu Buhari may have made a decision as to those...', '<div class="pf-content"><p style="text-align: justify;">There are strong indications that President Muhammadu Buhari may have made a decision as to those that will make up the next set of ministerial nominees to be sent to the Senate for screening.</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>RELATED: <span class="item-title"><a href="http://www.thetrentonline.com/thelist-next-batch-may-reach-senate-on-tuesday-buhari/">#TheList: Next Batch May Reach Senate On Tuesday – Buhari</a></span></strong></p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">According to <a href="http://thenationonlineng.net/2nd-ministerial-list-oyinlola%E2%80%88akeredolu-ex-ui-vc-on-the-card-as-buhari-ponders-over-fresh-nominees/" target="_blank">The Nation</a>, high level lobbying is already going on as the President weighs his options as to who will make the list.</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">It would be recalled that the President on Wednesday, September 30, 2015 sent a list of 21 names to the Senate President for screening.</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>ALSO READ: <span class="item-title"><a href="http://www.thetrentonline.com/snapshot-senator-saraki-receives-buharis-ministerial-thelist-photos/" target="_blank">SNAPSHOT: Senator Saraki Receives Buhari’s Ministerial #TheList (PHOTOS)</a></span></strong></p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">According to the report, those that might make the list include in-law to the Imo State Governor, Uche Nwosu; former Osun State Governor, Olagunsoye Oyinlola; Scientist and innovator, Barth Nnaji; former President of the Nigerian bar Association (NBA), Oluwarotimi Akeredolu among others.</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">The report also stated that the President may be looking for a new Group Managing Director for the Nigerian National Petroleum Corporation (NNPC) after the current incumbent, Ibe Kachikwu was nominated, probably to act as the Minister of State for Petroleum Resources.</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">The states that are said to be involved in the intense lobbying are Ondo, Kogi, Abia, Enugu, Imo, Bayelsa, Borno, Cross River, Nasarawa, Yobe, Zamfara, Osun, Kaduna, Bauchi, Sokoto, Adamawa, Lagos.</p>\n</div><p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.thetrentonline.com/ministerial-nominees-okorochas-cousin-oyinlola-make-buharis-2nd-batch-reports/">Ministerial Nominees: Okorocha&#8217;s Cousin, Oyinlola Make Buhari&#8217;s 2nd Batch &#8211; Reports</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.thetrentonline.com">The Trent</a>.</p>\n', '2015-10-03 08:17:41', '2015-10-03 07:28:15', 10, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'http://www.thetrentonline.com/ministerial-nominees-okorochas-cousin-oyinlola-make-buharis-2nd-batch-', 0, 0, 0, '2015-10-03 08:17:41', 2, 1, NULL, 0, NULL, 'Ministerial-Nominees:-Okorocha’s-Cousin,-Oyinlola-Make-Buhari’s-2nd-Batch-–-Reports'),
