(88, 'BUSTED: True Identity Of Twitter User Who ‘Predicted’ Boko Haram Bombings REVEALED (DETAILS)', 'http://www.thetrentonline.com/?p=124651', 'Boko Haram,Terrorism,,', '<p>The social media have been awash with reactions from several users ever since a Twitter user with...', '<div class="pf-content"><p style="text-align: justify;">The social media have been awash with reactions from several users ever since a <a href="/man-who-predicted-abuja-boko-haram-bombings-on-twitter-comes-under-fire-look/" target="_blank">Twitter user with handle “@chimaokoro63” ‘predicted’ the Boko Haram</a> bombings that rocked Abuja on Friday, October 2, 2015.</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">@chimaokoro63 Thursday, October 1, 2015 wrote: “I pray for Nigeria: There will be a bomb blast n Abuja&Lagos, Boko Haram is going to attack and kill police_army_Navy their evils:”</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Barely a day after his supposed ‘prediction’, <a href="/update-18-confirmed-dead-41-injured-in-abuja-boko-haram-bombings-details/" target="_blank">the Kuje and Nyanya areas of Abuja were attacked by Boko Haram insurgents leaving scores dead</a>.</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">The man had initially changed his handle from @chimaokoro63, to @chimaokori633 but subsequently deleted the account Saturday, October 3, 2015 after several users attacked him and called on security agents to arrest him.</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">However, the man’s mobile telephone number was later gotten on Facebook.</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">A probe of the number on True Caller application however, revealed that the user’s name is Sadiq Hono, apparently not even from South East descent as indicated by his Twitter handle.</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">The brow raising discovery has caused a fresh stir across the social media with a handful of users wondering if the said man is a member of the dreaded Boko Haram sect.</p>\n<p>One user wrote: “Boko Haram using an Igbo name” while